programme.desc: An ordinary suburban couple discover that their hospitable new neighbors are actually government spies. Soon, all four of them are caught up in an international espionage imbroglio

programme.title: Invictus
programme.desc: "Invictus" tells the inspiring true story of how Nelson Mandela joined forces with the captain of South Africa's rugby team, Francois Pienaar to help unite their country. Newly elected President Mandela knows his nation remains racially and economically divided in the wake of apartheid. Believing he can bring his people together through the universal language of sport, Mandela rallies South Africa's underdog rugby team as they make an unlikely run to the 1995 World Cup Championship match

programme.title: Volcano
programme.desc: Action flick about an emergency chief and a geologist who scramble to halt the destruction of L.A. from a volcanic eruption

programme.title: CHIPS
programme.desc: A maverick motorbike racer reeling from a divorce and a California Highway Patrol cop who's secretly an FBI operative must overcome their personality mismatch and work together to uncover a major theft in this big-screen adaptation of the famous TV series from the 1970s and '80s

programme.title: The Royal Tenenbaums
programme.desc: Offbeat comedy about a successful attorney who returns to the embittered and dysfunctional family he abandoned, claiming to have only six weeks to live. His sincere desire for forgiveness soon begins to have a profound effect upon the tortured and eccentric Tenenbaum clan

programme.title: Sixteen Candles
programme.desc: On the eve of her sister's wedding, suburban teenager Samantha suffers silently as her family forgets her birthday. Even worse, some total dork keeps propositioning her with sophomoric innuendo when she really craves romantic attention from high-school hunk Jake. Moving from Samantha's family home as it's invaded by outre relatives to a high-school dance where nothing seems to go her way, this bittersweet teen comedy traces the hopes and disappointments not only of Samantha..

programme.title: Girl with a Pearl Earring
programme.desc: During the 1660s, a teenage maid (Scarlett Johansson) in the Netherlands becomes a model for painter Johannes Vermeer (Colin Firth). Absorbing and visually rich; the film nicely captures Vermeer's artistic process. Tom Wilkinson. The film scored three Oscar nominations, including Best Cinematography. Peter Webber's directorial debut. Based on the novel by Tracy Chevalier

programme.title: The Alamo
programme.desc: With Dennis Quaid and Billy Bob Thornton in the cast, this historical drama features magnificent war scenes as it reconstructs the revolution over the independence of Texas, in 1836 –before, during and after the construction of the Alamo (a fort built by Spanish missionaries to catechize the natives). Texans and Tejanos (born in Mexico), led by William Travis, Davy Crockett (Thornton) and Jim Bowie, are besieged by an army commanded by Mexican dictator Antonio Lopez de Santa Ana. Later, however, the outcome of the battle of San Jacinto, under General Sam Houston (Dennis Quaid), is the defeat of the Santa Ana men, which finally leads to the independence of the state

programme.title: Driving Miss Daisy
programme.desc: A Southern matron forges a bond with her black chauffeur in the racially-divided 1960s South. Only when he is retired and she is confined to a home for the elderly do the two fully realize that they've been friends and kindred spirits all along

programme.title: Four Christmases
programme.desc: When their annual vacation getaway falls through, a happily unmarried couple are forced to spend Christmas with the families of their four divorced parents on the same day

programme.title: Sister Act
programme.desc: After witnessing her gangster boyfriend commit a murder, lounge singer Deloris evades capture and the police hide her in a convent. While adjusting to her new conditions, Deloris helps transform the choir, thus attracting a lot of attention

programme.title: La La Land
programme.desc: Struggling actress Mia and aspiring jazz pianist Sebastian begin a whirlwind romance as they both pursue their dreams in Los Angeles. However, their blossoming relationship is challenged when their careers pull them in different directions

programme.title: Never Been Kissed
programme.desc: Drew Barrymore enchants as a Chicago newspaper editor who relives her hellish teen years while on an undercover assignment at a local high school. Barrymore's great, but the film celebrates the fact that her character wins over the same type of “in crowd” that taunted her as a teen. David Arquette costars as her cool brother. Raja Gosnell is the director, and Barrymore served as executive producer

programme.title: Why Him?
programme.desc: An adoring dad is horrified to discover that his daughter's tech-billionaire boyfriend is a tattooed, party-hearty lout. Despite the latter's heart of gold, the father refuses to warm to him—especially when he learns about his engagement plans

programme.title: Whip It
programme.desc: Bliss Cavendar (Ellen Page) es una joven que crece en un pequeño pueblo de Texas, entre los partidos de fútbol de su padre Earl (Daniel Stern) y los concursos de belleza de su madre (Marcia Gay Harden). Un panorama desolador. Bliss está harta de todo eso y encuentra consuelo en su amiga Pash (Alia Shawkat), quien le propone una opción para escapar de ese mundo de tristeza y entender el sentido real de la vida

programme.title: The Breakfast Club
programme.desc: Teen-angst comedy drama. Five total strangers - an athlete, a spoiled rich kid, a brainy nerd, an introverted loner and a rebellious punk - are brought together on a day-long detention where they break the rules, bare their souls and find they have more in common than just attending the same high school. One of the plethora of 80s teen films, John Hughes's bittersweet 'brat pack' comedy has many perceptive moments

programme.title: Class Action

Holbrook: Larry Fishburne. Quinn: Donald Moffat. Pavel: Jan Rubes. Brian: Jonathan Silverman. Directed by Michael Apted

programme.title: The Mummy Returns
programme.desc: Adventurer Rick O'Connell (Brendan Fraser) once again battles the resurrected mummy in this sequel to the 1999 hit. Loud, absurd escapist fare with kitschy special effects. Evelyn “Evie” O'Connell: Rachel Weisz. Jonathan Carnahan: John Hannah. Stephen Sommers directed

programme.title: The Last of the Mohicans
programme.desc: During the French and Indian War, a European man raised Mohican rescues and escorts the daughters of a British colonel, on their way to their father at Fort Henry

programme.title: Selena
programme.desc: Biopic of the Tejano singer who was gunned down by an assistant at the height of her fame. The focus is primarily on Selena's relationship with her family, including her demanding manager-father, and her rise to stardom

programme.title: An Innocent Man
programme.desc: Tom Selleck plays a California airline mechanic sent to prison on trumped-up drug charges. Virgil: F. Murray Abraham. Kate: Laila Robins. Mike: David Rasche. Danny: Richard Young. John: Badja Djola. Robby: Todd Graff. Malcolm: M.C. Gainey. Directed by Peter Yates

programme.title: Crimes and Misdemeanors
programme.desc: A married New York ophthalmologist tries to break up with his mistress, who threatens to tell his wife. Meanwhile, his mob-connected brother offers to "make the problem go away."

programme.title: Happy Tears
programme.desc: Sisters Jayne (Parker Posey) and Laura (Demi Moore) reunite in Pittsburgh to care for their father, whose poor health hasn't stopped him from pursuing a romance with a suspicious woman (Ellen Barkin), much to the consternation of the two sisters. Rip Torn

programme.title: Lucas
programme.desc: Teen charmer about friendships and first loves among a trio of high schoolers

programme.title: Everything Must Go
programme.desc: An alcoholic businessman holds a garage sale after being fired from his job and thrown out of the house along with his belongings by his fed-up wife. While living on his front lawn, he unexpectedly makes friends with a neighbourhood kid and tries to reconnect with a girl he loved in high school

programme.title: Nocturnal Animals
programme.desc: An art-gallery owner reads a novel written by her ex-husband, and becomes greatly disturbed by the possibility that the story was inspired by their marriage and that her safety is in jeopardy

programme.title: The Outsiders
programme.desc: Members of rival local gangs, distinguished by the haves and the have-nots, get into a scuffle that results in death in 1960s Oklahoma

programme.title: Hoffa
programme.desc: The life of powerful union leader Jimmy Hoffa is the subject of this biographical drama. The focus is strongly on Hoffa's public and political life, from his early days as a labour organizer to his later conflicts with the Federal government -- and, eventually, his mysterious disappearance. A film based on the story of legendary union figure Jimmy Hoffa

programme.title: Hoffa
programme.desc: The life of powerful union leader Jimmy Hoffa is the subject of this biographical drama. The focus is strongly on Hoffa's public and political life, from his early days as a labour organizer to his later conflicts with the Federal government -- and, eventually, his mysterious disappearance. A film based on the story of legendary union figure Jimmy Hoffa

programme.title: Cake
programme.desc: A woman suffering from chronic pain starts seeing hallucinations of a young wife who committed suicide. Later, she gets to know the latter's husband and faces her own inner demons

programme.title: The Big Lebowski
programme.desc: Jeff Bridges is Jeff 'The Dude' Leboswki who's mistaken for Jeffrey Lebowski, who is The Big Lebowski. Which explains why he's roughed up and his rug pissed on. In search of recompense, The Dude tracks down his namesake, who instead offers him a job. His wife has been kidnapped and he needs a reliable bagman. Aided and hindered by his pals Walter Sobchak, a Vietnam vet, and Donny, master of stupidity, The Dude finds himself involved in violence, mayhem and bowling rivalry with Jesus Quintana in another Coen Brothers classic

programme.title: Adaptation
programme.desc: A screenwriter tries to adapt a bestseller about a real-life orchid thief, but his neuroses get in the way of his writing. When his identical twin brother moves in and decides to become a writer, Charlie finds it even harder to finish his screenplay, a challenge made worse by his growing obsession with the original work's author

programme.title: Adam
programme.desc: This character study stars Hugh Dancy as Adam, a man living with Asperger's syndrome, who does his best to reach out to his pretty new upstairs neighbor. As Adam attempts to gain control of his social skills, he discovers that with a little patience and understanding, developing a meaningful relationship might not be as hard as he previously thought. Peter Gallagher, Amy Irving, Rose Byrne

programme.title: Nell
programme.desc: A young woman living in an isolated North Carolina cabin is discovered by a small-town doctor, who is fascinated by her and attempts to introduce her to the world. Based on the play "Idioglossia" by Mark Handley

programme.title: Elizabeth
programme.desc: Cate Blanchett reprises her role as Queen Elizabeth I in this account of her efforts to defend England from King Philip II of Spain, while trying to suppress her attraction to the dashing Sir Walter Raleigh

programme.title: The Book of Eli
programme.desc: Post-apocalyptic action about a solitary warrior who fights to protect the last known copy of a powerful book. Decades after a nuclear war, a lone man calling himself Eli trudges through the dilapidated cities and scorched wilderness of America, carrying his copy of the Bible, a sacred book that provides 'contentment for the weak-minded'. Jerry Welbach (Pitt) is a low-level Mafia "mechanic" whose ineptitude is countered by frequent (but unpredictable) bursts of dumb luck. Jerry's girlfriend Samantha (Roberts) wants him to get out of the business, and after his latest blunder lands capo Arnold Margolese (Gene Hackman) in jail, so does mid-level crime kingpin Bernie Nayman (Bob Balaban). But Bernie insists that Jerry do one last errand for the mob before they let him find employment elsewhere -- he has to go to Mexico and recover a rare and very valuable pistol, which is said to be cursed. Once in Mexico, Jerry finds the pistol easily enough, but making his way back to the States proves to be an unexpected challenge

The group set out in a rescue bid, with Hud recording everything as they make their way through what has become a nightmarish New York, threatened both by the monster (only ever half-glimpsed, making it even more terrifying) and the parasitic lice it sheds, which develop a taste for human flesh. programme.title: The Taking of Pelham 1 2 3
programme.desc: The late Tony Scott's remake of the 1974 thriller, starring John Travolta and Denzel Washington. It's a day that the passengers on a New York subway train are unlikely to forget. And it's one that could rescue the professional life of subway employee Walter Garber, whose glittering career has been derailed by allegations of corruption. Garber is languishing on duty as a train dispatcher when all hell breaks loose after one of the Lexington Avenue line trains is hijacked by a gang led by the supremely self-assured, calmly ruthless Ryder. Ryder issues a demand for $10m and makes it clear that he won't hesitate to kill anyone who gets in his way. Garber and NYPD hostage negotiator Lieutenant Camonetti attempt to get to grips with the crisis but, as events progress, suspicions arise as to whether there's more to the hijacking than first meets the eye. Also starring James Gandolfini as New York's mayor and Luis Guzmán as a disgruntled subway worker who has joined Ryder's gang(n)
